In Mexico the ecological the agreement CE-CCA-00140 establishes the ecological criteria for water quality, and the limits necessary for drinking water and protection of aquatic life are:
Phosphates, 0.1 mg/L (for drinking water)
Nitrates, 5 mg/L (for drinking water)
Dissolved oxygen, 4 mg/L (for drinking water)
